Likewise, such a device destroys a row in the cpfrTrafficClassStatusTable when a TC has been purged from the system.

cpfrTCStatus.name: cpfrTCStatus
cpfrTCStatus.description: This object indicates the current state of a TC. 'default' The state means that the parent IP routes control the exit for this destination prefix. This would be the same behavior as if PfR were not configured or was shutdown. 'choose' The state indicates PfR is choosing the exit for the prefix. 'holddown' The state is seen when a TC is initially controlled by PfR. This holddown concept is applied to prevent churning or erratic behavior of PfR managed routes from being injected and withdrawn from the IP routing table (and subsequently being redistributed by some IGP) or BGP tables. 'inpolicy' This state means that the prefix meets the policy associated with this prefix or application. 'oopolicy' The prefix or application has been identified as failing to meet its respective policy.

cpfrTCSType.name: cpfrTCSType
cpfrTCSType.description: This object indicates whether a TC was learned or configured. 'learned' The TC is learned by PfR. 'configured' The TC is configured via CLI command.

cpfrTCSLearnListIndex.name: cpfrTCSLearnListIndex
cpfrTCSLearnListIndex.description: This object indicates the index of the learn list responsible for PfR learning this TC.

cpfrTCSTimeOnCurrExit.name: cpfrTCSTimeOnCurrExit
cpfrTCSTimeOnCurrExit.description: This object indicates the length of time the TC has been controlled on the current exit.

cpfrTCSControlState.name: cpfrTCSControlState
cpfrTCSControlState.description: The object indicates the control state of a TC. 'controlled' PfR is controlling this TC. 'uncontrolled' PfR is not controlling this TC.

cpfrTCSControlBy.name: cpfrTCSControlBy
cpfrTCSControlBy.description: This object indicates which routing protocol a TC is being controlled by. 'static' TC is controlled by static routing protocol. 'eigrp' TC is controlled by EIGRP. 'ribpbr' TC is controlled by RIB. 'bgp' TC is controlled by BGP 'pbr' TC is controlled by PBR. 'cce' TC is controlled by CCE. 'unknown' TC os controlled by unknown protocols

cpfrTCSTimeRemainCurrState.name: cpfrTCSTimeRemainCurrState
cpfrTCSTimeRemainCurrState.description: This object indicates the time remaining before the prefix timer expires.

cpfrTCSLastOOPEventTime.name: cpfrTCSLastOOPEventTime
cpfrTCSLastOOPEventTime.description: This object indicates the time when the last out-of-policy event was observed.

cpfrTCSLastOOPReason.name: cpfrTCSLastOOPReason
cpfrTCSLastOOPReason.description: This object indicates the last out-of-policy reason. This object indicates the reason that causes an out-of-policy event. 'delayOOPassiveMode' The Delay is out of policy in passive mode. 'lossOOPassiveMode' The loss is out of policy in passive mode. 'unreachableOOPassiveMode' The unreachability rate is out of policy in passive mode. 'delayOOPActiveMode' The Delay is out of policy in active mode. 'lossOOPActiveMode' The loss is out of policy in active mode. 'unreachableOOPActiveMode' The unreachability rate is out of policy in active mode. 'jitterOOPActiveMode' The jitter is out of policy in active mode. 'mosOOPActiveMode' The mos is out of policy in active mode. 'none' no reason. 'rsvpRecomputeExclude' The TC was excluded by recomputing RSVP bandwidth.

cpfrTCSLastRouteChangeEvent.name: cpfrTCSLastRouteChangeEvent
cpfrTCSLastRouteChangeEvent.description: This object indicates the value of sysUpTime when the last route change occurred for this TC.

cpfrTCSLastRouteChangeReason.name: cpfrTCSLastRouteChangeReason
cpfrTCSLastRouteChangeReason.description: This object indicates the reason the last route change occurred.

cpfrTrafficClassMetricTable.name: cpfrTrafficClassMetricTable
cpfrTrafficClassMetricTable.description: This table lists the TC's metrics instances created by the system. This table has an one-to-one relationship with cpfrTrafficClassTable, containing a row for each entry in cpfrTrafficClassTable.

cpfrTrafficClassMetricEntry.name: cpfrTrafficClassMetricEntry
cpfrTrafficClassMetricEntry.description: An entry describing the metric for a PfR monitored or controlled TC. A device supporting PfR creates a row in a cpfrTrafficClassMetricTable when it recognizes the addition of a new TC. Likewise, such a device destroys a row in the cpfrTrafficClassMetricTable when a TC has been purged from the system.

cpfrTCMLastUpdateTime.name: cpfrTCMLastUpdateTime
cpfrTCMLastUpdateTime.description: This object indicates the value of sysUpTime when the metrics were last updated.

cpfrTCMAge.name: cpfrTCMAge
cpfrTCMAge.description: This object indicates the age of a metric.

cpfrTCMetricsValid.name: cpfrTCMetricsValid
cpfrTCMetricsValid.description: This object indicates if an object in the entry is valid. 'relativeDelay' Relative delay is a valid value. 'relativeJitter' Relative jitter is a valid value. 'relativeDelayLoss' Relative loss is a valid value. 'relativeDelayUnreachable' Relative unreachability rate is a valid value. 'activeDelay' Absolute delay is a valid value. 'activeJitter' Absolute jitter is a valid value. 'activeLoss' Absolute loss is a valid value. 'activeUnreachable' Absolute unreachable rate is a valid value. 'mosPercentage' Most percentage is a valid value. 'attempts' The number of attempts is a valid value. 'packets' Probe packet is a valid value. 'passiveSTUnreachableAvg' Short time unreachability rate in passive mode is a valid value. 'passiveSTDelayAvg' Short time delay in passive mode is a valid value. 'passiveSTLossAvg' Short time loss in passive mode is a valid value. 'activeSTUnreachableAvg' Short time unreachability rate in active mode is a valid value. 'activeSTDelayAvg' Short time delay in active mode is a valid value. 'passiveLTUnreachableAvg' Long time unreachability rate in passive mode is a valid value. 'passiveLTDelayAvg' Long time delay in passive mode is a valid value. 'passiveLTLossAvg' Long time loss in passive mode is a valid value. 'activeLTUnreachableAvg' Long time unreachability rate in active mode is a valid value. 'activeLTDelayAvg' Long time delay in active mode is a valid value.

cpfrTCMActiveSTJitterAvg.name: cpfrTCMActiveSTJitterAvg
cpfrTCMActiveSTJitterAvg.description: This object indicates average jitter of a TC in active mode.

cpfrTCMMOSPercentage.name: cpfrTCMMOSPercentage
cpfrTCMMOSPercentage.description: This object indicates the number of Mean Opinion Score (MOS) packets with a percentage below threshold in active mode.

cpfrTCMAttempts.name: cpfrTCMAttempts
cpfrTCMAttempts.description: This object indicates the number of attempts to send an active probe to a target for this TC.

cpfrTCMPackets.name: cpfrTCMPackets
cpfrTCMPackets.description: This object indicates the number packets per jitter probe.

cpfrTCMPassiveSTUnreachableAvg.name: cpfrTCMPassiveSTUnreachableAvg
cpfrTCMPassiveSTUnreachableAvg.description: This object indicates the number of the average short term unreachable targets in passive mode.

cpfrTCMPassiveSTDelayAvg.name: cpfrTCMPassiveSTDelayAvg
cpfrTCMPassiveSTDelayAvg.description: This object indicates the short term delay as measured by Netflow. The short term interval is 5 minutes.

cpfrTCMPassiveSTLossAvg.name: cpfrTCMPassiveSTLossAvg
cpfrTCMPassiveSTLossAvg.description: This object indicates the number of short term packets lost in passive mode.

cpfrTCMActiveSTUnreachableAvg.name: cpfrTCMActiveSTUnreachableAvg
cpfrTCMActiveSTUnreachableAvg.description: This object indicates the number of short term unreachable packets in active mode.

cpfrTCMActiveSTDelayAvg.name: cpfrTCMActiveSTDelayAvg
cpfrTCMActiveSTDelayAvg.description: This object indicates the short term delay in milliseconds in active mode.

cpfrTCMPassiveLTUnreachableAvg.name: cpfrTCMPassiveLTUnreachableAvg
cpfrTCMPassiveLTUnreachableAvg.description: This object indicates the number of long term unreachable packets in flows-per-million in passive mode.

cpfrTCMPassiveLTDelayAvg.name: cpfrTCMPassiveLTDelayAvg
cpfrTCMPassiveLTDelayAvg.description: This object indicates the long term delay in milliseconds in passive mode.

cpfrTCMPassiveLTLossAvg.name: cpfrTCMPassiveLTLossAvg
cpfrTCMPassiveLTLossAvg.description: This object indicates the number of packets lost over the long term in packets-per-million in passive mode.

cpfrTCMActiveLTUnreachableAvg.name: cpfrTCMActiveLTUnreachableAvg
cpfrTCMActiveLTUnreachableAvg.description: This object indicates the number of long term unreachable packets in flows-per-million in active mode.

cpfrTCMActiveLTDelayAvg.name: cpfrTCMActiveLTDelayAvg
cpfrTCMActiveLTDelayAvg.description: This object indicates the long term delay in milliseconds in active mode.

cpfrLinkGroupExitTable.name: cpfrLinkGroupExitTable
cpfrLinkGroupExitTable.description: This table lists the link group instances created by the system. It has an expansion dependent relationship on cpfrExitTable, containing zero or more rows for each cpfrExitEntry.

cpfrLinkGroupExitEntry.name: cpfrLinkGroupExitEntry
cpfrLinkGroupExitEntry.description: An entry describing a link group configured for a PfR monitored or controlled external exit. A peer SNMP entity may create a link group for a PfR monitored or controlled exit by setting an instance of cpfrLinkGroupRowStatus to 'createAndWait' or 'createAndGo'. Observe that an implementation that does not support these option must specify these limitations in an agent capability statement. Other management entities (e.g., the local console) may create a link group for a PfR monitored or controlled external exit. In these cases, the system must automatically create a row in the cpfrLinkGroupExitTable. A peer SNMP entity may destroy a link group from a PfR monitored or controlled external exit by setting the corresponding instance of cpfrLinkGroupRowStatus to 'destroy'. Observe that an implementation that does not support this option must specify this limitation in an agent capability statement. Other management entities may destroy a link group from a PfR monitored or controlled external exit. In these cases, the system must automatically destroy the corresponding row in the cpfrLinkGroupExitTable. The system automatically destroys rows when the system or EMS/NMS destroys the corresponding entry in cpfrExitEntry.

cpfrLinkGroupName.name: cpfrLinkGroupName
cpfrLinkGroupName.description: This object indicates the name of a link-group.

cpfrLinkGroupIndex.name: cpfrLinkGroupIndex
cpfrLinkGroupIndex.description: This object indicates a unique arbitrary number identifying a specific instance in a link-group with the identical name.

cpfrLinkGroupStorageType.name: cpfrLinkGroupStorageType
cpfrLinkGroupStorageType.description: This object specifies the memory realization of the row. The following columnar objects are allowed to be writable when the storageType of this entry is permanent(4): cpfrLinkGroupBRIndex, cpfrLinkGroupExitIndex.

cpfrLinkGroupRowStatus.name: cpfrLinkGroupRowStatus
cpfrLinkGroupRowStatus.description: This object specifies the status of a NBAR application list. The following columnar objects must be valid in order to transition the row to the active state: None. The following columnar objects can be modified when the row is in the active state: None

cpfrLinkGroupBRIndex.name: cpfrLinkGroupBRIndex
cpfrLinkGroupBRIndex.description: This object specifies the PfR BR on which the exit related to this link group is configured.

cpfrLinkGroupExitIndex.name: cpfrLinkGroupExitIndex
cpfrLinkGroupExitIndex.description: This object specifies the exit, identified by this index, in combination with cpfrLinkGroupBRIndex, in cpfrExitTable.

cpfrLinkGroupType.name: cpfrLinkGroupType
cpfrLinkGroupType.description: This object indicates PfR Link-Group type. 'primaryLinkGroup' primary link-group 'fallbackLinkGroup' fallback link-group 'none' There is no link-group.

cpfrNbarApplListTable.name: cpfrNbarApplListTable
cpfrNbarApplListTable.description: This table lists the NBAR list instances created by the system. This table has an expansion dependent relationship on cpfrMatchTable and cpfrLearnListTable, containing zero or more rows for each cpfrMatchEntry and cpfrLearnListEntry.

cpfrNbarApplListEntry.name: cpfrNbarApplListEntry
cpfrNbarApplListEntry.description: An entry describing a NBAR application configured in PfR. A peer SNMP entity may create an NBAR application entry by setting an instance of cpfrNbarApplListRowStatus to 'createAndWait' or 'createAndGo'. Observe that an implementation that does not support these option must specify these limitations in an agent capability statement. Other management entities (e.g., the local console) may create a NBAR application. In these cases, the system must automatically create a row in the cpfrNbarApplListTable. A peer SNMP entity may destroy a NBAR application by setting the corresponding instance of cpfrNbarApplListRow Status to 'destroy'. Observe that an implementation that does not support this option must specify this limitation in an agent capability statement. Other management entities may destroy an NBAR application. In these cases, the system must automatically destroy the corresponding row in the cpfrNbarApplListTable. The system automatically destroys rows when the system or EMS/NMS destroys the corresponding entry in cpfrMatchEntry and cpfrLearnListEntry.

cpfrNbarApplListName.name: cpfrNbarApplListName
cpfrNbarApplListName.description: This object indicates the name of a NBAR application list.

cpfrNbarApplIndex.name: cpfrNbarApplIndex
cpfrNbarApplIndex.description: This object indicates a unique arbitrary number identifying a specific protocol in a PfR NBAR Application List.

cpfrNbarApplListStorageType.name: cpfrNbarApplListStorageType
cpfrNbarApplListStorageType.description: This object specifies the memory realization of the row. The following columnar objects are allowed to be writable when the storageType of this conceptual row is permanent(4): cpfrNbarApplPdIndex.
